"title": "7734: leaders, spiritual",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7734: leaders, spiritual",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Under the old covenant God called priests and prophets as spiritual leaders. Later the Pharisees gave spiritual leadership. After Jesus Christ had inaugurated the new covenant, authority was given to the apostles, who in turn appointed leaders in the churches they founded.</p>\n<h2>Priests as spiritual leaders</h2>\n<h3>They were called by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:4\">HEB 5:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:1\">EXO 28:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:5\">DEU 18:5</a></p>\n<h3>The high priest represented the people in the presence of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:1\">HEB 5:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:29-Exod28:30\">EXO 28:29–28:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:21\">NUM 27:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:3\">HEB 8:3</a></p>\n<h3>Priests taught and explained God's law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:7\">MAL 2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:11\">LEV 10:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:11-Hag2:13\">HAG 2:11–2:13</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of priests as spiritual leaders</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam4:18\">1SA 4:18</a> <em>The priest Eli was described as leading Israel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:5-1Sam7:9\">1SA 7:5–7:9</a> <em>Samuel acted as priest on behalf of the people</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:14\">2CH 24:14</a> <em>Jehoiada the priest influenced Joash to serve God.</em></p>\n<h2>Prophets as spiritual leaders</h2>\n<h3>They were called by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:21\">2PE 1:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:8-Isa6:9\">ISA 6:8–6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:5\">JER 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of prophets as spiritual leaders</h3>\n<p>Samuel led the people from idolatry back to the worship of God:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:3-1Sam7:4\">1SA 7:3–7:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:20-1Sam12:24\">1SA 12:20–12:24</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:18-1Kgs18:21\">1KI 18:18–18:21</a> <em>Elijah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:7-Hag1:9\">HAG 1:7–1:9</a> <em>Haggai</em></p>\n<h2>Spiritual leaders in NT times</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:4\">MAT 2:4</a> <em>officially recognised teachers of the law</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:1\">MAT 16:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:23\">MAT 21:23</a> <em>At a local level, elders had social and religious authority in local councils. Nationally, they were included in the Sanhedrin</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:2\">MAT 23:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:59\">MAT 26:59</a></p>\n<h2>The failure of spiritual leaders</h2>\n<h3>In the OT</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:7\">ISA 28:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:11\">JER 23:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:13-Jer23:17\">JER 23:13–23:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:25-Jer23:32\">JER 23:25–23:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:1-Mal2:2\">MAL 2:1–2:2</a></p>\n<h3>In the NT</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:4-Matt23:15\">MAT 23:4–23:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:42-Mark10:45\">MRK 10:42–10:45</a> <em>Jesus Christ taught his disciples the qualities required for spiritual leadership.</em></p>\n<h2>Spiritual leadership in the church</h2>\n<h3>The apostles delegated authority</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:34-Acts4:35\">ACT 4:34–4:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:2-Acts6:3\">ACT 6:2–6:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:23\">ACT 14:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:5\">TIT 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>The qualifications for church leadership</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:1-1Tim3:9\">1TI 3:1–3:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:6-Titus1:9\">TIT 1:6–1:9</a></p>\n<h3>Advice to leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:31\">ACT 20:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:35\">ACT 20:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:17-1Tim5:20\">1TI 5:17–5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2-1Pet5:3\">1PE 5:2–5:3</a></p>",
